
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Person {
  +firstName: String
  +familyName: String
  +birthDate: Date
  -id: UUID (derived from unique key)
}

class Trainer {
  +diploma: String
}

class Member {
  +isProspect: Boolean
}

class FitnessCenter {
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class Room {
  +number: Integer
  +maxCapacity: Integer
}

class Session {
  +date: Date
  +startTime: Time
}

class GroupSession {
  +type: String
}

class IndividualSession {
  ' No additional attributes needed
}

' Inheritance relationships
Person <|-- Trainer
Person <|-- Member

FitnessCenter "1" *-- "many" Room : has
Room "1" *-- "many" Session : hosts

Session <|-- GroupSession
Session <|-- IndividualSession

' Associations
Member "0..*" --> "1" Session : participates in
Trainer "0..*" --> "1" GroupSession : supervises

GroupSession "1" --> "1" Room : held in
IndividualSession "1" --> "1" Room : held in

' Constraints:
' - Each session is associated with one room of a specific center.
' - At most one session per room at a given time.
' - A person can be both trainer and member.
' - Prospects and interns are modeled via flags.

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`**: Abstract base class containing common attributes (first name, last name, birth date).
- **`Trainer` and `Member`** inherit from `Person`. A person can be both a trainer and a member.
- **`FitnessCenter`** has many **`Room`s**, each with a number and max capacity.
- **`Session`** is an abstract base class with two subtypes:
  - **`GroupSession`** requires a trainer and a type.
  - **`IndividualSession`** has no trainer.
- A **`Room`** can host multiple **`Sessions`**, but only one per start time and date.
- **`Member`** can participate in any session. The `isProspect` flag marks people not yet registered for sessions.
- **`Trainer`** may supervise group sessions; the `diploma` field distinguishes trainers even if they haven't supervised any session yet.

